{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then Job answered,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "“I have heard many such things. You are all miserable comforters!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Shall vain words have an end? Or what provokes you that you answer?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I also could speak as you do. If your soul were in my soul’s place,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I could join words together against you,\nand shake my head at you,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "but I would strengthen you with my mouth. The solace of my lips would relieve you."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "“Though I speak, my grief is not subsided. Though I forbear, what am I eased?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But now, God, you have surely worn me out. You have made all my company desolate."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "You have shriveled me up. This is a witness against me. My leanness rises up against me."
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "It testifies to my face."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He has torn me in his wrath and persecuted me. He has gnashed on me with his teeth."
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "My adversary sharpens his eyes on me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "They have gaped on me with their mouth. They have struck me on the cheek reproachfully."
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "They gather themselves together against me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "God delivers me to the ungodly, and casts me into the hands of the wicked."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I was at ease, and he broke me apart. Yes, he has taken me by the neck, and dashed me to pieces."
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He has also set me up for his target."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "His archers surround me. He splits my kidneys apart, and does not spare."
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He pours out my bile on the ground."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He breaks me with breach on breach. He runs at me like a giant."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I have sewed sackcloth on my skin, and have thrust my horn in the dust."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "My face is red with weeping. Deep darkness is on my eyelids,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "although there is no violence in my hands, and my prayer is pure."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "“Earth, don’t cover my blood. Let my cry have no place to rest."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Even now, behold, my witness is in heaven. He who vouches for me is on high."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "My friends scoff at me. My eyes pour out tears to God,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "that he would maintain the right of a man with God, of a son of man with his neighbor!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For when a few years have come, I will go the way of no return."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}